 in some jurisdictions. It is more urgent than ever to engage in productive discussion, which begins with being informed about content that is still scarcely understood outside small industry and fan circles. Erotic Comics in Japan: An Introduction to Eromanga is the most comprehensive introduction in English to erotic comics in Japan, or eromanga. Divided into three parts, it provides a history of eroticism in Japanese comics and cartoons generally leading to the emergence of eromanga specifically, an overview of seven themes running across works with close analysis of outstanding examples and a window onto ongoing debates surrounding regulation and freedom of expression in Japan.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aErotic comic books, strips, etczJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aErotic drawing. 0aErotic literature, Japanese. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aAsian Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 4aMedia Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Japanese.2bisacsh  aJapan, comics, sexuality.1 aBauwens-Sugimoto, Jessica.1 aGalbraith, Patrick.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048550722423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048550722/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK